WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
Water Damage Categories classify the contamination level of water intrusion.

00:08.000 --> 00:16.000
Category 1 is clean water from a sanitary source.

00:16.000 --> 00:24.000
Category 2 is grey water with significant contamination.

00:24.000 --> 00:32.000
Category 3 is black water, heavily contaminated and potentially toxic.

00:32.000 --> 00:40.000
Correct classification determines safety protocols, drying procedures, and documentation requirements.

00:40.000 --> 00:48.000
RestoreAssist guides you through classification with built-in decision trees and ensures your documentation reflects the correct category.